 Firefighters in the Eden District Municipality were fighting three fires yesterday, while mop-up operations took place in nine hotspots.
The municipality said priority areas included the Molen River, Kubuku and De Vlugt on the Keurbooms River east of George in the Langkloof.
Eden disaster management head Gerhard Otto said about 300 firefighters, the majority from Working on Fire, had been deployed in the area.
Farmers had also pitched in.
“Without the farmers working together and assisting all the firefighters, we would have struggled to contain the fires raging since November 1,” Otto said.
Late yesterday, some fires were getting closer to houses he said.

